I’m reaching out because your career trajectory is the closest real-world example I’ve found to what I’m building toward.
My background is in risk analytics across derivatives and capital markets — I currently work on XVA pricing, FRTB, and CCR simulation. But increasingly, the part of the work I’m drawn to isn’t the delivery side. It’s the validation side. Every time I interact with a model, I find myself questioning the assumptions, stress-testing the edge cases, and wanting to own the independent challenge — not just consume the output.
That shift in mindset is what’s pushing me toward model risk and validation as a deliberate career move. I’m already investing in the technical foundations — FRM, quantitative coursework — but I know that credentials alone don’t make the transition credible.
What would make it credible is understanding how someone who’s actually done it thinks about the craft. That’s why I’m reaching out.
If you have 20 minutes at any point, I’d genuinely value your perspective.
